    "blog_two_col_qa_1": {
      "type": "blog-two-column-text",
      "name": "Blog: Two Column Text",
      "settings": {
        "width": "wrapper",
        "max_width": 1100,
        "gap": 120,
        "left_heading": "",
        "left_text": "<p>YOU’VE TRAVELED THE WORLD—AND YET YOU KEEP RETURNING TO YOUR HOME, ITALY. WHAT MAKES IT DIFFERENT FROM OTHER PLACES?</p>",
        "left_text_style": "h4",
        "left_italic": false,
        "right_heading": "",
        "right_text": "<p>For me Italy is the best, most wonderful theater in the world—an open-air theater where everybody can decide what role to play. And I have decided to play the Explorer of Beauty.</p><p>As Italians, beauty is in our DNA. We have the good fortune to be born in a place where we are surrounded by art. Maybe we just get used to the beauty immediately and then we can’t live without it.</p>",
        "right_text_style": "body",
        "right_italic": true,
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
    "blog_quote_two_images_rNJW4c": {
      "type": "blog-quote-two-images",
      "name": "Blog: Quote + Two Images",
      "settings": {
        "width": "wrapper",
        "max_width": 1100,
        "gap": 56,
        "left_image": "shopify://shop_images/Roberto_Coin_Image3.png",
        "quote": "<p>“I FIND BEAUTY EVERYWHERE,” HE SAYS, “IN NATURE, IN PEOPLE, IN ARCHITECTURE, IN ART AND IN FOOD.”</p>",
        "quote_max_width": 520,
        "right_image": "shopify://shop_images/Roberto_Coin_Image4.png",
        "left_media_height": 760,
        "right_media_height": 380,
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
    "blog_two_column_text_AhcBci": {
      "type": "blog-two-column-text",
      "name": "Blog: Two Column Text",
      "settings": {
        "width": "wrapper",
        "max_width": 1100,
        "gap": 120,
        "left_heading": "",
        "left_text": "<p><strong>What Inspired You to Turn That Appreciation for Beauty Into Your Life's Work? When Did You First Consider Designing Jewelry?</strong></p>",
        "left_text_style": "h4",
        "left_italic": false,
        "right_heading": "",
        "right_text": "<p>As a child, I spent every summer with my grandmother in the countryside near Venice. It’s a beautiful area where the houses have been built along the banks of the Brenta Riviera. Where nature dictates the pace, typical of life in the countryside.</p><p>Every day, as I was running around with the other children, I used to stop and look at this little workshop—Elsa’s Atelier. Inside, I could see colored fabrics, women absorbed in their work, creating fashion, pinning and unpinning, sewing and tailoring. It looked like an incredible world to me and I was extremely curious. I learned a lot. I saw how to create an object from a wish, how to sketch, how to choose fabrics and about the harmony of colors and shapes. All of this inspired me deeply.</p><p>I fell in love, and, as I was very strong-minded, found a way to enter this world and become part of it.</p>",
        "right_text_style": "body",
        "right_italic": false,
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
    "brand_story_combo_7Wt6rb": {
      "type": "brand-story-combo",
      "name": "Story Layout Bundle",
      "settings": {
        "layout": "image-right",
        "width": "wrapper",
        "top_heading": "<p><strong>AND TO DO THAT YOU HAD TO TRAVEL THE WORLD?</strong></p>",
        "top_text": "<p>To learn properly the trade, I had to travel around the world. I visited over a thousand factories, some Italian, some foreign, and met many different maestros. They were extremely interesting to me. But in the end, it was clear that I had to be different. I had to be myself. I had to be Roberto.</p>",
        "top_image": "shopify://shop_images/Roberto_Coin_Image5.png",
        "caption_text": "",
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
